race.comment: MILLENNIUM BLADE (4) resumes looking very well placed. Three runs last time in were in good 2yo company, third in a high rating race on debut and placing in his next two thereafter. Comes back to a maiden for the first time and with even luck getting across from the gate he should go close. FORCEOFONE (2) struck a tough track at Pakenham second up and can be excused for going under at $1.90. The fresh run was good and he can bounce right back here. MISS ELLANEOUS (11) was just fair fresh at Geelong in a strong maiden, but the winner there has won a strong race since. She was in the market there and can improve quickly. TAN TAT ART (14) is a Flying Artie filly on debut who can run well.
